I get the same problem. I am using a 1.5 VM and get the error message in the details pane when trying to look at a HashMap or Properties file.

Casting "this" to "Map" seems to be a workaround. This is the formatter that I use: (for objects of type "Map")

int max = ((Map) this).size() - 1;
StringBuffer buf = new StringBuffer();
Iterator it = ((Map) this).entrySet().iterator();

buf.append("{");
for (int i = 0; i <= max; i++) {
    Map.Entry e = (Map.Entry) (it.next());
        Object key = e.getKey();
        Object value = e.getValue();
        buf.append((key   == this ? "(this Map)" : key) + "=" +
                   (value == this ? "(this Map)" : value));

    if (i < max)
	buf.append(",\n");
}
buf.append("}");
return buf.toString();

